What Companies Actually Evaluate

Most backend interviews (especially Node.js / TypeScript roles) evaluate 4 pillars:

  • Coding / Problem Solving
    • Basic algorithms (not hardcore competitive level)
    • Data handling
    • Clean logic

  • Backend Fundamentals
    • APIs
    • Databases
    • Authentication
    • Error handling

  • System Design (Entry → Mid level)
    • How you structure a service
    • How you think about scaling
    • Trade-offs

  • Communication (Very underrated)
    • Clarity
    • Structured thinking
    • Explaining decisions

